text: Few movies give me chills but this was one of them. Great choice in casting here as was a pleasant suprise. No one really annoyed me much. The MI6 Kingsman organization seemed as it should.   A throwback to a bygone era perhaps.  But one which very well may be needed again today.   Jackson fit the eccentric,  environmentalist, super geek nut case. Which i never much trusted any of those types anyways.    Gazelle was clearly the best villain sidekick ever I think!!  She seemed to be the real brains behind the operation though.   In the backgroud but clearly in control. An interesting character of which i would like to know more of a backstory on.   Sofia Boutella i have known about for awhile now.  She is also in real life an extremly gifted dancer, and  performer. Who i didn't at first reconize until a friend pointed it out.  Great movie, casting and overall enjoyable film.  :b

text: After watching this movie, I'm feeling a bit fulfilled, excited and just wanna go watch it again, and again. This movie has no shortness of suspense, more than enough action, sensible story, great plots, great scenes, and everything just actually makes sense. After watching the failures of earlier 2015 movies, I must say, in a long time, (probably since "The Matrix", or more recently "Ironman 1") this is the first movie I would actually give a 10 out of 10. I am so happy he didn't bag the recruited chick at the end, that would have just been cliche and ruin the ending. Being in the technology field, my senses and imagination ran wild this entire movie, even in "downtime", I could follow and relate to just about everything from gadgets to advanced weaponry. to sum it up in two words... LOVED IT! If you haven't seen it yet, and like movies like "The Matrix", "Branded", "Ironman", "PreDestination" and/or "Thor" (not the sequels), then you will most definitely love this movie! Go See it, Download it or Buy It!

text: Having seen the trailer and read a couple of reviews for Kingsman: The Secret Service i wasnt expecting too much from this film but i actually thought it was a lot of fun. Sure , it has quite a few faults ( which film doesn't ? ) and it's extremely silly but the action is very good and at no stage was i bored. It's a cross between Spy Kids , James Bond and Austin Powers and it's strange to see Colin Firth involved in something so left of field but he does a pretty good job. The language is pretty raw through out so it's not something the kids or granny should watch , which is a shame because apart from that and the violence it's a very childish film.  7 out of 10
